.TH "rdma_query_gid" 9 "rdma_query_gid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_query_gid \- Read the GID content from the GID software cache
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rdma_query_gid
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "union ib_gid *gid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
Device to query the GID
.IP "port_num" 12
Port number of the device
.IP "index" 12
Index of the GID table entry to read
.IP "gid" 12
Pointer to GID where to store the entry's GID
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBrdma_query_gid\fP only reads the GID entry content for requested device,
port and index. It reads for IB, RoCE and iWarp link layers.  It doesn't
hold any reference to the GID table entry in the HCA or software cache.

Returns 0 on success or appropriate error code.
